00:20:29.504 --> 00:20:31.420
KRISTINE MCDIVITT TOMPKINS:
Well, as you said,

00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:37.860
I grew up on a ranch where my
great grandfather-- he founded

00:20:37.860 --> 00:20:38.360
it.

00:20:38.360 --> 00:20:39.810
And my grandfather
was born there.

00:20:39.810 --> 00:20:41.000
Our father was born there.

00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:42.710
We were born there.

00:20:42.710 --> 00:20:49.450
So we were sort of hooligans,
as ranching kids often are,

00:20:49.450 --> 00:20:50.590
and outside a lot.

00:20:50.590 --> 00:20:54.820
But I don't think that my
sensibilities toward nature

00:20:54.820 --> 00:20:55.870
really started there.

00:20:55.870 --> 00:20:58.840
Maybe it made me more
comfortable in it.

00:20:58.840 --> 00:21:03.280
We moved to Venezuela when I was
eight years old for three years

00:21:03.280 --> 00:21:05.990
and then came out of there.

00:21:05.990 --> 00:21:08.110
And that was probably
the first time

00:21:08.110 --> 00:21:14.260
that I was exposed to so many
species that, as a Californian,

00:21:14.260 --> 00:21:15.820
you'd never see.

00:21:15.820 --> 00:21:17.080
And they were right there.

00:21:17.080 --> 00:21:18.210
It was not in Caracas.

00:21:18.210 --> 00:21:22.250
We were way out in
the Orinoco Basin.

00:21:22.250 --> 00:21:23.330
I don't know.

00:21:23.330 --> 00:21:28.290
I think Yvon had a
huge impact on my life.

00:21:28.290 --> 00:21:31.190
I met him when I was 15.

00:21:31.190 --> 00:21:38.680
And once you get into
the climbing tribe,

00:21:38.680 --> 00:21:40.930
I don't think-- it's
