00:27:37.210 --> 00:27:39.820
you name it.

00:27:39.820 --> 00:27:42.010
The company is really
on the front lines.

00:27:42.010 --> 00:27:45.610
And I think that's
the value system

00:27:45.610 --> 00:27:48.500
that we've had
since the beginning,

00:27:48.500 --> 00:27:50.210
but it's absolutely clear.

00:27:50.210 --> 00:27:53.210
I just came from a two-day
Patagonia board meeting.

00:27:53.210 --> 00:27:57.780
And it's full of these
discussions about,

00:27:57.780 --> 00:28:01.800
how do you keep pushing the line
out, asking more of yourself,

00:28:01.800 --> 00:28:09.250
asking more of customers,
in terms of educating them,

00:28:09.250 --> 00:28:13.930
and will they join us as
the lawsuit was placed

00:28:13.930 --> 00:28:17.150
against the government having to
do with public lands and Bears

00:28:17.150 --> 00:28:18.370
Ears?

00:28:18.370 --> 00:28:22.090
And the response to those
things has been extraordinary.

00:28:22.090 --> 00:28:31.400
So they still run the
company as a means

00:28:31.400 --> 00:28:34.130
to build the greatest
products, which has always

00:28:34.130 --> 00:28:40.220
been Yvon's desire, but also
to use the company absolutely

00:28:40.220 --> 00:28:43.760
as a mechanism to
change the world.

00:28:43.760 --> 00:28:46.970
And that has-- if I close
my eyes at a board meeting

00:28:46.970 --> 00:28:49.300
and I listen to
Yvon speak, it could

00:28:49.300 --> 00:28:53.170
have been 45 years ago
when we got going together.

00:28:53.170 --> 00:28:55.850
He is very consistent.

00:28:55.850 --> 00:29:01.730
And I think that's just an
extraordinary and unusual set

00:29:01.730 --> 00:29:03.110
of circumstances.

00:29:03.110 --> 00:29:05.480
SPEAKER: Yeah, absolutely.

